        <h3 data-uuid="117ac0e181ac4c1b8cb4e9ef16def052">The
            Delegates Gather</h3>
        <p data-uuid="84382e562c484e0aa7cf3be18d6302e4">In February 1787 the Confederation Congress invited each
            state to send delegates to a convention in Philadelphia. The <b><dfn title="Constitutional Convention">Constitutional
            Convention</dfn> </b>was held in May 1787 in
            Philadelphia's Independence Hall. The goal of the meeting was to improve the
            Articles of Confederation.</p>
        <p data-uuid="e4f6cc331e1849708d3f407282ecab28">Several major issues divided the delegates to the
            Constitutional Convention. Some members wanted only small changes to the
            Articles of Confederation, while others wanted to rewrite the Articles
            completely. In the end, the delegates would leave with an entirely new U.S.
            Constitution. This decision angered some of the participants.</p>
        <p data-uuid="8d23aa6d95804ba0b9d386982bed7532">
            Most
            delegates were well educated, and many had served in state legislatures or
            Congress. Benjamin Franklin and <b><dfn title="Madison, James">James Madison</dfn></b> were there. Revolutionary
            War hero George Washington was elected president of the Convention.</p>
        <section class="image-with-rich-media-hotspot" data-uuid="2ef5a0ad72144636be86e7c8f3b1a0e1">
            <object type="text/html" data="../../assets/widgets/image_hotspot_rich_media/index.html" class="widget" data-uuid="bbb428f957cb4794b5760bedd5a3413c">
