        <p data-uuid="ff4df2234cab4424879064e7edb792d3">Several important voices were absent. John Adams and Thomas
            Jefferson could not attend. Patrick Henry chose not to
            attend because he did not want a stronger central government. Women, African
            Americans, and Native Americans did not take part because they did not yet have
            the rights of citizens.<br />
        </p>
